  "source": "loan-policy.txt",
  "text": "Education Financing and Loan Policy\r\n\r\nTo improve accessibility, the academy may offer financing options through approved Non-Banking Financial Companies (NBFCs).\r\n\r\nLoan Eligibility\r\n\r\nLoan approval is based on multiple factors including:\r\n\r\n- Parent credit score\r\n- Income verification\r\n- Historical payment behavior\r\n- Internal risk assessment performed by the NBFC\r\n\r\nLoan Approval\r\n\r\nLoan approval is solely at the discretion of the financing NBFC.\r\n\r\nThe academy does not guarantee loan approval and has no authority to override the lender's decision.\r\n\r\nDisbursement\r\n\r\nUpon loan approval, the loan amount is paid directly by the NBFC to the academy.\r\n\r\nThe student subscription is activated only after successful loan disbursement.\r\n\r\nRepayment\r\n\r\nLoan repayment obligations exist solely between the parent and the NBFC.\r\n\r\nEMIs are typically collected through bank auto-debit, NACH mandate, UPI AutoPay, or other repayment mechanisms approved by the lender.\r\n\r\nRefund Restrictions\r\n\r\nSubscriptions funded through loans are not eligible for refunds under any circumstances.\r\n\r\nCancellation of a subscription does not automatically cancel the loan agreement.\r\n\r\nDispute Resolution\r\n\r\nAny dispute regarding loan approval, EMI schedules, interest calculations, penalties, or repayment terms must be addressed directly with the NBFC.\r\n\r\nIllustrative Interest Rate\r\n\r\nInterest rates may vary based on risk profile and lender policies. Typical annual interest rates may start at 10% per annum and may be higher depending on borrower eligibility.\r\n\r\nThe academy acts only as a facilitator and is not a party to the financing agreement between the parent and the NBFC.",
